'''''Battlefield V''''' is a [[first-person shooter]] [[video game]] developed by [[EA DICE]] and published by [[Electronic Arts]]. ''Battlefield V'' is the sixteenth installment in the ''[[Battlefield (video game series)|Battlefield]]'' series. It was released worldwide for [[Microsoft Windows]], [[PlayStation 4]], and [[Xbox One]] on November 20, 2018. Those who pre-ordered the Deluxe Edition of the game were granted early access to the game on November 15, 2018,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2018/10/18/complete-guide-to-battlefield-5-preorder-bonuses|title=Complete Guide to Battlefield 5 Preorder Bonuses|last=Macy|first=Seth G.|website=IGN|date=October 18, 2018|access-date=November 2, 2018}}</ref> and [[Origin Access]] Premium subscribers on PC received access to the game on 9 November 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.polygon.com/2018/11/9/18079060/battlefield-5-ea-subscribers-early-release-date|title=Players who buy Battlefield 5 have to wait the longest to play it|work=Polygon|access-date=2018-11-09}}</ref> The game is based on [[World War II]] and is a thematic continuation of its [[World War I]] based precursor ''[[Battlefield 1]]''.

Pre-release reception of the game was mixed, with the announcement trailer causing backlash from fans of the series for a perceived lack of historical accuracy and the inclusion of female soldiers. Upon release, ''Battlefield V'' received generally favourable reviews from critics. 

== Gameplay ==
''Battlefield V'' will focus extensively on party-based features and mechanics, scarcity of resources, and removing "abstractions" from game mechanics to increase realism.<ref name="vergereturn" /> There will be an expanded focus on player customization through the new [[Company (military unit)|Company]] system, where players will be able to create multiple characters with various cosmetic and weapon options. Cosmetic items, and currency used to purchase others, will be earned by completing in-game objectives.<ref name="polygoncustom">{{cite news|url=https://www.polygon.com/2018/5/23/17385040/battlefield-5-character-customization-items|last=Gilliam|first=Ryan|date=May 23, 2018|title=Players can customize every aspect of their characters in Battlefield 5|work=Polygon|access-date=May 24, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180530130700/https://www.polygon.com/2018/5/23/17385040/battlefield-5-character-customization-items|archive-date=May 30, 2018}}</ref><ref name="vergereturn" /><ref name="polygon-nopass" />

The game will feature several new multiplayer modes, including the "continuous" campaign mode "Tides of War", "[[Battle royale game|Firestorm]]", and "Grand Operations". The Grand Operations mode is an expansion of the "Operations" mode introduced in ''Battlefield 1'', which focuses on matches taking place across multiple stages to simulate a campaign from the war. In Grand Operations, each round will have specific objectives, and performance in each stage will influence the next. Games will culminate with a "Final Stand", with players using only a primary weapon with limited ammo, and no respawns. Similarly to ''Battlefield 1'', the game will feature a collection of single-player "war stories" based on aspects of World War II.<ref name="vergereturn">{{cite news|url=https://www.theverge.com/2018/5/23/17384042/battlefield-5-release-date-trailer-video|last=Savov|first=Vlad|title=Battlefield V returns to World War II this October|work=The Verge|date=May 23, 2018|access-date=May 23, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180530130250/https://www.theverge.com/2018/5/23/17384042/battlefield-5-release-date-trailer-video|archive-date=May 30, 2018}}</ref> The game also features a [[cooperative gameplay|cooperative]] mode not seen since ''[[Battlefield 3]]'' called "Combined Arms", where four players can undertake missions together and features dynamic missions and objectives so missions cannot be played the same way each time. Combined Arms is scheduled to be released after launch.<ref name="screenrant">{{cite news|url= https://screenrant.com/battlefield-v-co-op-campaign-combined-arms/|last=Treese|first=Tyler|date=May 23, 2018|title=Battlefield V 4-Player Co-op Campaign Combined Arms Revealed|work=Screen Rant|access-date=September 9, 2018}}</ref> The [[Battle royale game|Battle Royale]] mode will be built around the franchise's "core pillars of destruction, team play, and vehicles".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2018-06-09-battlefield-v-is-getting-a-battle-royale-mode-called-royale|title=Battlefield V is getting a battle royale mode called Royale|work=Eurogamer.net|access-date=June 14, 2018|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.trustedreviews.com/news/battlefield-5-release-date-3231890|last=|first=|title=Battlefield 5: EA announces Battle Royale mode at E3 2018|work=TrustedReviews|date=June 9, 2018|access-date=June 9, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/e3-2018-battlefield-5-battle-royale-mode-announced/1100-6459536/|last=|first=|title=E3 2018: Battlefield 5 Battle Royale Mode Announced By EA|work=GameSpot|date=June 9, 2018|access-date=June 9, 2018}}</ref> The name "Firestorm" is derived from a literal storm of fire that engulfs players similar to the popular Battle Royale game mechanic of restricting the play area. Furthermore, this particular game mode is not being developed by EA DICE themselves, but has been outsourced to [[Criterion Games]] and features the biggest map created by the franchise to date. It is playable by 64 players, which are divided into up to 16 squads with a focus on team work.{{cn|date=November 2018}} Firestorm is scheduled to be released in March 2019.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.pcgamer.com/battlefield-5s-battle-royale-mode-wont-be-live-until-spring-2019/|title=Battlefield 5's battle royale mode won't be live until spring 2019|work=PC Gamer|access-date=November 1, 2018|language=en}}</ref>

== Synopsis ==
As in ''Battlefield 1'', the single-player campaign is divided into episodic ''War Stories,'' three of which are available at launch: ''"Nordlys"'' takes place from the point-of-view of a [[Norwegian resistance movement|Norwegian resistance]] fighter taking part in the [[Norwegian heavy water sabotage|sabotage of the German nuclear program]], ''"Tirailleur"'' tells the story of a [[Senegalese_Tirailleurs|Senegalese Tirallieur]] during [[Operation Dragoon]], and ''"Under No Flag"'' puts the player in the shoes of Billy Bridger, a convicted bank robber and explosives expert conscripted into the [[Special Boat Service]] to take part in [[Operation Albumen]]. A fourth campaign, ''"The Last Tiger"'', will launch later.

== Development ==
DICE unveiled the first details surrounding ''Battlefield V'' on May 23, 2018, with more information to be unveiled during the EA Play press conference near [[E3 2018]] in June. DICE has stated that, unlike ''Battlefield 1'', it does not plan to use paid [[downloadable content]], or "[[loot box]]es" for non-cosmetic items within ''Battlefield V''; new content will be added to the game for all players over time (which, itself, will progress through the different stages of World War II), at no additional charge.<ref name="polygon-nopass">{{cite news|url=https://www.polygon.com/2018/5/23/17384662/battlefield-5-premium-pass|title=Battlefield 5 ditches the premium pass|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180524115940/https://www.polygon.com/2018/5/23/17384662/battlefield-5-premium-pass|archive-date=May 24, 2018|work=Polygon|access-date=May 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/2018/gaming/news/battlefield-v-details-1202819935/|title=‘Battlefield V’ Hits Oct. 19, Explores WWII Free of Premium Pass, Loot Boxes|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180524120154/http://variety.com/2018/gaming/news/battlefield-v-details-1202819935/|archive-date=May 24, 2018|last=Crecente|first=Brian|date=May 23, 2018|work=Variety|access-date=May 23, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> The decision to exclude these features was made following the outrage over the loot box system in ''[[Star Wars Battlefront II (2017 video game)|Star Wars Battlefront II]]'', another EA DICE title.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://kotaku.com/heres-our-first-look-at-battlefield-v-which-goes-back-1826271285|title=Here's Our First Look At Battlefield V, Which Goes Back To WWII|work=Kotaku|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180524115705/https://kotaku.com/heres-our-first-look-at-battlefield-v-which-goes-back-1826271285|archive-date=May 24, 2018|access-date=May 24, 2018|date=May 23, 2018|last=Scheirer|first=Jason}}</ref> The game was originally set to release on October 19, but was delayed to November 20 to enable the developers to "make some final adjustments to core gameplay".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pcgamer.com/battlefield-5-release-date-delayed-to-november/|title=Battlefield 5 release date delayed to November|publisher=}}</ref>

== Reception ==
=== Pre-release ===
The announcement trailer was met with a backlash from fans of the series who criticized the game for a lack of [[Historicity|historical accuracy]] and authenticity. Complaints were given to the use of certain weapons, [[Prosthesis|prosthetics]], and body art as being very uncommon in that time period.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kain|first1=Erik|title=This 'Battlefield 5' Reveal Trailer Has Me More Confused Than Hyped|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/erikkain/2018/05/23/battlefield-5s-reveal-trailer-has-me-more-confused-than-hyped/#7cb0098156f9|website=Forbes|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180525205623/https://www.forbes.com/sites/erikkain/2018/05/23/battlefield-5s-reveal-trailer-has-me-more-confused-than-hyped |archive-date=May 30, 2018|access-date=May 25, 2018}}</ref> Some fans were also frustrated with the portrayal of women in the game, specifically with the British woman featured in the trailer as British women never participated in frontline combat and were mostly relegated to supporting roles.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Groux|first1=Christopher|title='Battlefield V' Trailer Sparks Outrage, But Did Women Fight in World War II?|url=https://www.newsweek.com/battlefield-v-5-trailer-outrage-did-women-fight-world-war-2-943856|archiveurl=|archivedate=|website=Newsweek|access-date=September 1, 2018}}</ref> Although acknowledging that British women were rarely on the frontline, critics have responded that [[Women in World War II|female soldiers did participate in World War II]], highlighting real-life examples from multiple countries, and that previous games in the ''Battlefield'' series are not seen as a completely realistic portrayal of war. Some also suggested that the backlash was partly due to [[misogyny]], rather than genuine worries over historical accuracy.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Plunkett|first1=Luke|title=Oh No, There Are Women In Battlefield V|url=https://kotaku.com/oh-no-there-are-women-in-battlefield-v-1826275455|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180530135530/https://kotaku.com/oh-no-there-are-women-in-battlefield-v-1826275455|archive-date=May 30, 2018|website=Kotaku|access-date=May 25, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Martin|first1=Matt|title=Battlefield 5 has women in it. If that bothers you, please, piss off|url=https://www.vg247.com/2018/05/24/battlefield-5-women-bothers-please-piss-off/|archiveurl=|archivedate=|website=VG247|access-date=August 30, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Kim|first1=Matt|title=Battlefield 5 Doubles Down on the Representation of Women in World War II|url=https://www.usgamer.net/articles/battlefield-5-women-world-war-2|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180530135956/https://www.usgamer.net/articles/battlefield-5-women-world-war-2|archive-date=May 30, 2018|website=US Gamer|access-date=May 25, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Farokhmanesh|first1=Megan|title=Battlefield V fans who failed history are mad that the game has women in it|url=https://www.theverge.com/2018/5/24/17388414/battlefield-v-fans-game-women-world-war-2-history|archive-date=May 30, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180530140326/https://www.theverge.com/2018/5/24/17388414/battlefield-v-fans-game-women-world-war-2-history|website=The Verge|access-date=May 25, 2018}}</ref><ref name=TS>{{cite web|work=[[The Sun (United Kingdom)|The Sun]]|url=https://www.thesun.co.uk/tech/6369985/battlefield-5-notmybattlefield-russian-snipers-accuracy/|title=HARSH TRUTHS World War 2’s legion of female snipers make a mockery of Battlefield 5 complaints|last1=Coby|first1=Alex Asssoon|last2=Matheson|first2=Anna|date=May 24, 2018}}</ref>

In response to the outcry, the game's executive producer Aleksander Grøndal wrote on [[Twitter]] that the team would "always put fun over authentic."<ref>{{cite web|first=Shabana|last=Arif|title=Battlefield V Producer Says DICE Will 'Always Put Fun Over Authentic'|url=http://uk.ign.com/articles/2018/05/24/battlefield-v-producer-says-dice-will-always-put-fun-over-authentic|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180530140512/http://www.ign.com/articles/2018/05/24/battlefield-v-producer-says-dice-will-always-put-fun-over-authentic|archive-date=May 30, 2018|website=IGN|date=May 24, 2018|access-date=May 25, 2018}}</ref> DICE's general manager Oskar Gabrielson also responded on Twitter, saying "Player choice and female playable characters are here to stay ... Our commitment as a studio is to do everything we can to create games that are inclusive and diverse. We always set out to push boundaries and deliver unexpected experiences."<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kane |first1=Alex |title=EA DICE Exec Fires Back About Women in ‘Battlefield V' |url=https://variety.com/2018/gaming/news/battlefield-v-women-1202822531/ |website=Variety | date=May 25, 2018 | access-date=June 7, 2018 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180607153827/https://variety.com/2018/gaming/news/battlefield-v-women-1202822531/ | archive-date=June 7, 2018}}</ref> EA chief creative officer [[Patrick Söderlund]] said the developer was uninterested in taking flak for diversifying the gaming space. "We stand up for the cause, because I think those people who don’t understand it, well, you have two choices: either accept it or don’t buy the game," he said. "I’m fine with either or." Söderlund went on to say that the development team itself pushed for women in ''Battlefield V''.<ref name=TV>{{cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2018/6/12/17453728/ea-women-in-battlefield-v-backlash-response|title=EA on the backlash against women in Battlefield V: ‘Accept it or don’t buy the game’|last1=Farokhmanesh|first1=Megan|last2=Nicolett|first2=Megan|date=June 12, 2018}}</ref> In September, after the game was delayed by a month, DICE revealed they are planning on "dialing back" the character customization to attempt to "give more authenticity to the game", saying "We want players to be excited about customizing their characters with authentic gear. We dialed it back a bit. It was pretty crazy, We wanted to offer some authenticity, and that’s important to us, that’s important to our players.”<ref>{{cite web|title=DICE is “dialling back” Battlefield V’s character customisation|url=https://www.pcgamesn.com/battlefield-v/battlefield-v-authentic-customisation|last=Jones|first=Ali|publisher=''[[PCGamesN]]''|date=September 13, 2018|access-date=September 14, 2018}}</ref>

In August, the [[Cowen Group]], gaming industry analysts, reported that [[pre-order]] sales of ''Battlefield V'' were "weak", being 85% behind those of ''[[Call of Duty: Black Ops 4]]''.<ref name=G>{{cite web|date=August 17, 2018|title=Former DICE CEO Patrick Söderlund Leaves Studio; Reveals Pre-Orders for Battlefield V are ‘Weak’|last=Hossam|first=Mostafa|publisher=[[Complex (magazine)|Gameranx]]|url=http://gameranx.com/updates/id/159331/article/former-dice-ceo-patrick-soderlund-leaves-studio-reveals-pre-orders-for-battlefield-v-are-weak/}}</ref><ref name=CNBC>{{cite web|date=August 20, 2018|title=Analyst predicts EA's 'Battlefield V' will be a 'serious disappointment,' says preorders lag 'Call of Duty' by more than 85%|last=Kim|first=Tae|publisher=[[CNBC]]|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2018/08/20/cowen-predicts-eas-battlefield-v-will-be-a-serious-disappointment-citing-weak-pre-orders.html}}</ref>

=== Critical response ===
{{Video game reviews
| MC = (PC) 81/100<ref name="MCPC">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/battlefield-v |title=Battlefield V for PC Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=November 17, 2018}}</ref><br>(PS4) 73/100<ref name="MCPS4">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-4/battlefield-v|title=Battlefield V for PlayStation 4 Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=November 17, 2018}}</ref><br>(XONE) 79/100<ref name="MCXB1">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-one/battlefield-v |title=Battlefield V for Xbox One Reviews |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=November 17, 2018}}</ref>
| GI = 8/10<ref name="GI">{{cite web |last1=Bertz |first1=Matt |title=Battlefield V Review – Hedge Warfare |url=https://www.gameinformer.com/review/battlefield-v/battlefield-v-review-hedge-warfare |website=[[Game Informer]]|accessdate=November 25, 2018}}</ref>
| GRadar = {{Rating|3.5|5}}<ref name="GRadar">{{cite web|url=https://www.gamesradar.com/battlefield-5-review/|title=Battlefield 5 review: “Not as drastic a change up as its WW1 predecessor, nor as wild or wondrous”|last=Avard|first=Alex|work=[[GamesRadar+]]|date=November 9, 2018|access-date=November 25, 2018}}</ref>
}}
According to review aggregator [[Metacritic]], ''Battlefield V'' received "generally favourable" reviews for the PC and Xbox One versions and "mixed or average" reviews for the PlayStation 4 version.<ref name="MCPC"/><ref name="MCPS4"/><ref name="MCXB1"/>

In ''[[GameInformer]]''{{'}}s 8/10 review, they wrote, "Ultimately, ''Battlefield V'' will be defined by the success or failure of the pending Combined Arms cooperative mode, Firestorm battle royale mode, and whether or not DICE can continually provide new and engaging content."<ref name= GI/> ''[[GamesRadar+]]'' gave the game 3.5/5 stars, praising the gameplay but criticizing the online multiplayer, writing: "Not as drastic a change up as its WW1 predecessor, nor as wild or wondrous, ''Battlefield 5''{{'}}s deliberative design sidelines its strengths as a simulative sandbox."<ref name=GRadar/>

=== Sales ===

In November, it was reported that ''Battlefield V'' sold fewer than half the physical copies that ''Battlefield 1'' did upon its launch during the same period of time.<ref>{{cite web|title=Battlefield 5 physical sales down more than half on Battlefield 1|url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2018-11-26-battlefield-5-physical-sales-down-more-than-half-on-battlefield-1|last=Phillips|first=Tom|publisher=''[[Eurogamer]]''|date=November 26, 2018|access-date=November 28, 2018}}</ref>

